      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, basal insulin works differently than bolus insulin and is designed to provide a steady background level of insulin that helps regulate blood sugar between meals and during sleep. Skipping a dose of basal insulin is generally not recommended, as it significantly increases the risk of severe nocturnal hypoglycemia (dangerously low blood sugar) while you are asleep and cannot react quickly. If you suspect you are about to go low, follow your specific protocol for Taking Strict Order of Treatations, which likely involves checking your blood sugar first and then taking one-third of your rapid-acting dose, rather than skipping your required background medication.",
